## Churn and Risk Analysis

One customer has churned — **Patricia Kimani** (Bronze tier, Coventry) — representing a **6.7% churn rate**.

Risk scoring across the active customer base produced the following distribution:

| Risk Level | Customers | Score Range | Recommended Action |
|---|---|---|---|
| Critical | 1 | 80-100 | Urgent call + 50% discount |
| High | 2 | 60-79 | 20% discount voucher |
| Medium | 4 | 40-59 | Double loyalty points |
| Low | 5 | 20-39 | Monthly newsletter |
| Very Low | 3 | 0-19 | No action needed |

> **3 customers require immediate intervention** before they follow the churned customer out of the business.

